-- BP Awards Contract to Jacobs for Halt at Rotterdam Refinery Unit
-- B y   L a n a n h   N g u y e n
-- 2012-04-17T13:39:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/bp-awards-contract-to-jacobs-for-halt-at-rotterdam-refinery-unit.html
Jacobs Engineering Group Inc. (JEC)  will
work on a “major shutdown” of a unit at  BP Plc (BP/) ’s Rotterdam
refinery, its biggest plant in  Europe .  Jacobs will provide services for the project on a fluid
catalytic cracker unit, Jacobs said in a statement today,
without specifying the date or duration of the maintenance. FCC
units are used in gasoline production.  BP’s Rotterdam refinery is Europe’s second-largest, with a
capacity of 400,000 barrels a day. The FCC can process 62,000
barrels a day, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lananh Nguyen in London at 
